MALACAÑANG Manila

PROCLAMATION NO. 623

RESERVING FOR SCHOOL SITE PURPOSES OF THE MANAT BARANGAY HIGH SCHOOL A CERTAIN PARCEL OF LAND OF THE PUBLIC DOMAIN SITUATED IN BARANGAY MANAT, MUNICIPALITY OF NABUNTURAN, PROVINCE OF DAVAO DEL NORTE, ISLAND OF MINDANAO.

Upon recommendation of the Secretary of the Department of Environment and Natural Resources and by virtue of the powers vested in me by law, I, CORAZON C. AQUINO, President of the Philippines, do hereby withdraw from sale, entry, disposition or settlement and reserve for school site purposes of the Manat Barangay High School under the administration of the Department of Education, Culture and Sports, subject to private rights, if any there be, a certain parcel of land of the public domain situated in Barangay Manat, Municipality of Nabunturan, Province of Davao del Norte, Island of Mindanao, and more particularly described as follows:

Lot 5000-B, Csd-11-008664-D identical to Lot 12991, Pls-2 (Compostela Public Land Subdivision)

(MANAT BARANGAY HIGH SCHOOL)

A parcel of land, Lot 5000-B, Cad-11-008664-D identical to lot 12991, Pls-2, Compostela Public Land Subdivision, situated in Manat, Nabunturan, Davao del Norte, Island of Mindanao. Bounded on the Northeast along lines 5-6-7 by Road; on the Southeast along line 7-8 by Lot 5000-A, Csd-11-008664-D, (MANAT ELEMENTARY SCHOOL) identical to Lot 12990, Pls-2 Compostela Public Land Subdivision, on the Southwest along lines 8-9-10-11-1-2 by Road and on the Northwest along lines 2-3-4 by Road. Beginning from point marked “1” on plan, being S. 24 deg. 05′ E., 96.19 m. from BLLM No. 3, Pls-2, Compostela Public Land Subdivision.

3.88 m. to point 2;

3.72 m. to point 3;

139.97 m. to point 4;

3.42 m. to point 5;

3.57 m. to point 6;

108.08 m. to point 7;

149.90 m. to point 8;

6.77 m. to point 9;

6.55 m. to point 10;

9.74 m. to point 11;

90.27 m. to point of

beginning, containing an area of FIFTEEN THOUSAND EIGHT HUNDRED EIGHTY THREE (15,883) SQUARE METERS. All points referred to are indicated on the plan and are marked on the ground as follows: points 7 and 8 are PS Cyl. Conc. Mons., 15 x 40 cm. and the rest are OLD PLS Cyl. Conc. Mons., 15 x 60 cm. Bearing true, date of original survey October 1, 1952 to June 30, 1953, that of the subdivision survey January 17, 1985 by Geodetic Engineer Blas A. Caberte and was approved on March 11, 1989.

IN WITNESS WHEREOF, I have hereunto set my hand and caused the seal of the Republic of the Philippines to be affixed.

Done in the City of Manila, this 7th day of August , in the year of Our Lord, nineteen hundred and ninety.

(Sgd.) CORAZON C. AQUINO

By the President: (Sgd.) CATALINO MACARAIG, JR. Executive Secretary

